This is a embedded pong game featuring two-board interactions and graphical animation design. Users can tilt the board to move the paddle using the IMU sensor and hit the ball. 
The board communication is done through UART and there are also some intercommunications between peripherals and MCU through SPI and I2C. The demonstration can be found 
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5wKXYSq8LO4
